RISING star, Peter Okputu aka Oluwajah has explained why he featured popular Nigerian musician Oritsefemi on the remix of his single, Naso. The Afro Pop cum Highlife artist disclosed this in a chat with The Nation recently.   AMAA, StarTimes to splash N6.5m on filmmakers at 2022 short…     Deb China serenades with Maradona     My encounter with strange lady changed my life, says…   He said, “Oritsefemi has the tenacity to woo one’s attention with his motivational words of wisdom underlaid with his rich unique motivational melodious sound”. Speaking on the song, Oluwajah who is currently working on his forthcoming Extended Play (EP) with producers such as Speroach beats, Magicboi and Boombeatz, said Naso is a message to his fans to always stay true to themselves and believe in the good life has to offer, despite the trying times in the country. “I would love the support system from both families, friends, fans, the music industry and cooperate bodies blossom; and be more cooperative regardless of status, religion and tribe. We all need to work together as a team with a strong sense of understanding together we would harness a better music industry”, said Oluwajah.